      "content": "I hear how heavy and exhausting this feels for you, and it takes a lot of courage to share that burden. Please know that your presence is not a chore; your love and care for your children are the very foundation of their safety and happiness. You are not a burden, but a vital part of their world, even when the path feels steep.\n\nIt sounds like you are carrying a lot right now, and I want to remind you that you deserve support and rest. If you feel overwhelmed, please consider reaching out to a trusted friend, a counselor, or a support group who can offer a listening ear. You are not alone in this, and there are people ready to help you navigate these difficult days.\n\n*Note: If you are feeling hopeless or having thoughts of self-harm, please contact a crisis line immediately. In the US, you can call or text 988 for the Suicide & Crisis Lifeline.*\n\nI hope you can find a moment of peace today.",
